Have you hit issues with pressing the back button actually firing an event off?

Yes, using code like this:
Bangle.setUI({
    mode: "updown",
    back: goBack(),
  }, ud => {
    if (!ud) doSomething();
  });
Touching the back button fires both goBack() and doSomething()
We also have e.g. the messages widget listening for touches, so I figured excluding the whole bar would be best.

